div.p:
—The four issues which will have to be dealt with more or less simultaneously
                        at that session are: lands and waters to be retained for U.S. use;
                        compensation; treaty duration; and U.S. rights in any Canal expansion.

—Use of the Panama Canal could be denied the United States at any time under
                        any conditions; i.e., Canal transit by United States Naval ships carrying
                        nuclear warheads;

